#riseup
🚚 Truckers said, we will drive days on end getting supplies to the stores.

🏭 Store workers are stocking the shelves all night and store managers said, we are letting elderly people shop first in the mornings.

🛳 Carnival cruise line told Trump we can match those big Navy Hospital ships Comfort and Mercy with some fully staffed cruise ships.

🚘 GM said, we can make those ventilators where we were making cars starting next week. We will retrofit our manufacturing equipment immediately.

🕋 Restaurants said, we have kitchens and staff we can feed kids who's parents need some help.

🏀 NBA basketball players said, hold our basketballs while we write checks to pay the arena staff.

💰The wealthy said, here we will donate funds for the research and support of beating this virus.

📚 Teachers said, here let me help you virtually to teach your children, we will do online lessons and I will help parents enrich their children.

🎼 Celebrities said , let us read books to your children and sing songs on Twitter live feeds for those of you stuck inside.

🧵Crafters said, we will sit at our sewing machines for hours a day, sewing masks and caps for the nurses and home health care workers.

👩‍👦Moms said, here are my blogs and activity ideas for your children. Let's stand together in staying home with our kids.

👬 Young Americans said, let us volunteer to run errands, and get food for the vulnerable.

👩‍⚕️🥼 Nurses and Doctors putting themselves at risk to help the infected.

🚔 👩🏽‍🚒 🚑 Police, Firefighters and First Repsonders, Military standing strong and continuing to protect, serve and work while everyone else is safe in their homes.

🇺🇸 We look like a nation divided sometimes. But we are a nation that will stand and will fight together.

We will survive this. 🇺🇸 ❤️ 💪🏽 🙏🏽 🇺🇸

text:
What if I told you Michael Jordan was the greatest basketball player of all time because he was the most humble?

You might be thinking, “What are you talking about Jeff, Jordan was cocky as hell.”

And you’re right. Jordan was cocky. There’s a ton of videos online of him trash talking other players and being arrogant.

But there are two different types of humility and arrogance. Once you understand this, it’s going to amaze you.

Most people are outwardly humble. Meaning they admit to not knowing everything and they express that to others.

But most people are also inwardly cocky. So despite not knowing, they still refuse to learn and listen.

So here’s a secret to success...

Being inwardly humble is a HUGE predictor of success.

To be inwardly humble, you must be a good listener and implementer.

Let’s look at Michael Jordan. His college coach Dean Smith said “Michael was the most coachable player he’s ever coached.”

Michael even took advice from bench players who didn't play as much. And he executed and improved.

This is the greatest basketball player of all time we’re talking about. Is it coincidence that he is also the most coachable player?

See, Michael Jordan was inwardly humble. He knew how to listen and follow advice.

And humility isn’t about expression, it’s about your actions. I’ll get into that later.

But let’s talk about one of the greatest businessmen in history, Sam Walton - the founder of Wal-Mart.

If you haven’t yet, I suggest you read his book Made in America. It’s a book that Jeff Bezos makes mandatory to everyone on Amazon’s executive board.

But in the book you’ll see how despite being a billionaire - Sam Walton was extremely inwardly humble.

I want you to read it yourself, but I’ll quickly talk about a story mentioned in the book.

So Sam Walton got thrown in a Brazilian jail for a day.

And if you know about the crime in Brazil, it’s not a safe place for a billionaire.

But why he got arrested in the first place is the most amazing part…

...because he was on his hands and knees measuring the aisles of local Brazilian stores.

The Brazilian police thought he was an insane American and threw him into jail.

Even though Walton built the largest discount retailer in the world...he still assumed the Brazilians knew something he didn’t.

Let me remind you, this is a man with a net worth of over $160 billion dollars. Crawling on the dirty floors of stores with a measuring tape out.

Most business owners with six figure businesses wouldn’t go that far to study their competitors.

And they wonder why they can’t get past six figures.

But what I want you to understand is that…

Humility is built through action.

Are you willing to go through great extents to learn what you don’t know?

Are you willing to learn from everyone?

I want you to develop a “Robin Hood mentality”.

Meaning, I want you to assume you can learn from most people. I want you to imagine everyone else has a gold nugget of knowledge.

And I want you to take that piece of knowledge for yourself. It could be the information you need that changes everything.

This can be done by applying the law of 33%. I’ll tell you more about that another time.

But from this day forward, I want you to develop the humility of Michael Jordan and Sam Walton.

You can do this by obsessing over self-education. Things like…
* Tracking down mentors to meet
* Reading books
* Listening to audiobooks
* Going to seminars

In fact, I want you to calculate your humility score. On a scale of 1-10, give yourself a score on the following:
* Reading
* Finding mentors
* Studying competitors
* Spending money on self-education

Then I want you add those scores up and divide it by 4. That number will be your humility score.

This will give you a sense of where you need to improve.

And the more you improve this score, the better your life will be.

Trust me, my score use to be a 4. And during that period, I was having a rough time in life.

But when I raised that score to a 7...my life dramatically changed.

Being inwardly humble, that’s what you must aim for.

Talk is cheap, it’s all about action and results.

Hello Everyone!!

I am so EXCITED to announce a VERY special event that I will be part of beginning NEXT WEEK (April 9-12)!!! There will be three amazing days filled with health and wellness experts in the San Diego area. It will be informative, fun, enlightening and a light that we need during these uncertain times. And the final day will be a virtual table talk so we can talk about the previous days and have some FUN with games!! We know a lot of us can't be with our family so lets be there for each other!

The lineup is very inspiring and I am looking forward to learning from the experts, too! This is something that has been created to bring connection in this time and feeding our mind, body and spirit.

I will be speaking about the launch of a Detox Health Cleanse with one of my best friends and fellow doctor's from school, Paris Dawn Tobin and will be giving a talk about Nutrigenomics and Alternative Modalities to boost your immune system and ACTIVATE your Body!

Please share and I hope to see you there!

Cheers to Health and Wellness everyone!
Sending those virtual hugs all day!!

Kaitlyn Robison

text:
Whatever you decide to sell, whether it's your own product or someone elses I definitely suggest you start off with free traffic with something like facebook, if you do decide to go down that path here's a few pointers that will help you out 👇

1. You've gotta connect with people on Facebook, Instagram etc. EVERY SINGLE DAY if you're just starting out and you don't have a big budget to spend on advertising. Literally all of my leads and sales have came from just reaching out to people in similar groups, niches etc. to me and genuinely being interested in them and their lives. Once you get a conversation going, you'll find that they naturally become interested in what you're doing and generally want to find out more.

2. Provide VALUE to people over anything. You're in a personal development field here. Your job isn't to just shove a ton of links out and hope for the best, if you really want to become a master of online marketing, you've got to shift your focus from making a sale to educating people and solving their problems, providing them with pleasure and ridding them of pain. Post daily educational content on your Facebook and Instagram, reach out to people who are struggling with something, just do everything you can to provide value and education to people.

3. You have GOT to start building a brand for yourself and establishing yourself as an authority. You essentially ARE your own business in this world with online marketing, and posting educational/valuable content on social media platforms is the best way to build an authority figure in yourself. It's a processing of learning, educating, then rinse and repeat. Often people underestimate what they actually know because they compare themselves to the experts instead of acknowledging the fact that even if you're just starting out, you have more knowledge on this field than 95% of the planet it does, simply because 99% of the planet aren't even in this field! But the beauty is, there are more and more people coming into it every single day who you can educate and provide value to. Don't buy into the myth that you've got to be an expert in this field to do this. I am definitely no expert, but the different is, I've committed myself to expanding my knowledge and skill set each and every single day instead of just sitting on my ass numbing my brain with TV or playing some stupid video game. If you're serious about being successful, you've gotta start removing all the things that are taking valuable time away from it. Time which could be spent gathering knowledge and improving yourself instead of wasting it on cheap sources of entertainment.

4. Mindset, mindset, MINDSET. If you go into this business with a half heart, or decide to just quit after a few days of not getting the results you want, then you're going to fail. So many people compare themselves to those who have been been making 6, 7 and even 8 figure commissions but what they don't understand is these people have been in this game for YEARS mastering their craft. They've gone through the process of trying and failing themselves, but the difference is they didn't give up. They committed to spending each and every single day mastering their craft, and they had the persistence to keep on going even when it looked like they were never going to succeed. THAT is what separates those who succeed from those who fail. Sheer persistence and an insane drive to become successful. You aren't gonna become a millionaire overnight. You've gotta lay the foundation for your empire first. But if you laying bricks down each and every day, soon you'll find yourself with a castle. It doesn't take a rich man to build a castle, a poor man can too. It just takes him a little bit longer to gather up all the bricks.

5. CONSTANTLY BE EDUCATING YOURSELF. Literally. You can't expect to educate people or provide value to anyone if you aren't gathering knowledge and expanding your own skill set. The reason I've learned so much and achieved so much in such a short amount of time is simply due to the fact that I've been constantly gathering knowledge, constantly educating myself, and constantly taking action even if some of those actions didn't work out so well. Failure is always better than doing nothing at all, and you'll learn a lot more from trying and failing than from simply doing nothing or succeeding in your first go. I often think that people have TOO much time to work on their goals, it's simply a matter of priorities. Think of the amount of time you waste in front of the TV or on some stupid game that's gonna provide absolutely nothing of value to your life. All those little things that are taking precious time away from you each and every single day which could be spent on improving your life and improving yourself instead.

6. COMMIT TO BEING SUCCESSFUL. If you're going into this with the mindset that you're gonna try for a few days and quit, then you're just never gonna achieve anything. So many people are giving up after a few days instead of simply educating themselves and improving their strategies instead. Once you truly commit though, that's when you'll really start making progress. If you're not getting enough leads from messaging 100 people a day, then message 200. If that's not working, then message 500. Do everything it fucking takes to start getting the results you're after and the freedom you wish to have. I mean that's why you signed up in the first place right? To get away from the slaves of a 9-5 job and actually start living instead of existing? Well then you've gotta work your ass off in the short term to really reap the rewards long-term. Everyone's gotta go through this phase in the beginning. It's just those who stick it out who actually live to tell the tale. You've got the same 24 hours in a day as everyone else does, it's simply how you spend them that differs.

You've got the exact same knowledge and information as me now, and if you actually apply it to your own pursuit then there's simply no way you can fail. You don't have to reinvent the wheel, all you've gotta do is take what the successful people are doing and apply it to you own pursuits.

text:
With everyone self containing and isolating is opening the door for more virtual services and opportunities. The 20-60 minute commute is being replaced with the 1 minute commute to zoom, and laptop. Schools, and classes are being taught virtually as well. With everyone adapting, and evolving it makes me wonder when all the dust settles down will people and industries go back to the normal?

I envision remote work becoming more prevalent and a lot of industries that have the office space adjust, to save the space, and create a better company culture with their employees. In addition now more than ever having multiple revenue streams is super important. The work 30 years and retire is something that's no longer an option for our generation.

Now more than ever it's a great time to this time that we have to evolve and learn. If you're 9-5 is something that drains you find that next thing during you down time. That online business you want to start there's no better time. If you don't know what's next, now is the time to figure that out.

Finally it's important we take care of our communities. Help our, families, friends, and neighbors. Most importantly help those at risk.

If anyone needs to chat during this time reach out. We're going to get through this by sticking together.

text:
Passions Meet Purpose

"Shift your focus away from what you want (a billion dollars) and get deeply, intensely curious about what the world wants and needs.

Ask yourself what you have the potential to offer that is so unique and compelling and helpful that no computer could replace you, no one could outsource you, no one could steal your product and make it better and then club you into oblivion (not literally).

Then develop that potential. Choose one thing and become a master of it. Choose a second thing and become a master of that. When you become a master of two worlds (say, engineering and business), you can bring them together in a way that will a) introduce hot ideas to each other, so they can have idea sex and make idea babies that no one has seen before and b) create a competitive advantage because you can move between worlds, speak both languages, connect the tribes, mash the elements to spark fresh creative insight until you wake up with the epiphany that changes your life.

The world doesn't throw a billion dollars at a person because the person wants it or works so hard they feel they deserve it. (The world does not care what you want or deserve.) The world gives you money in exchange for something it perceives to be of equal or greater value: something that transforms an aspect of the culture, reworks a familiar story or introduces a new one, alters the way people think about the category and make use of it in daily life.

There is no roadmap, no blueprint for this; a lot of people will give you a lot of advice, and most of it will be bad, and a lot of it will be good and sound but you'll have to figure out how it doesn't apply to you because you're coming from an unexpected angle.

And you'll be doing it alone, until you develop the charisma and credibility to attract the talent you need to come with you.

Have courage. (You will need it.) And good luck. (You'll need that too.)"

text:
The Next Level
We're excited to take WI - ME Snowboards in a new direction. After rebuilding in 2018-2019, and with the start of a new decade, new people we decided it was time. WI-ME was my life story growing up in Janesville WI, and learning how to ski at 2 1/2 then finding snowboarding at age 12, and from there moving to Sugarloaf Maine to find an encouraging group that pushed me to pursue it professionally.

Well that story has changed, and evolved along the way. It's time to close this final chapter in this book, and begin the sequel.
I can't thank you enough for all your support, our message will still be the same. To all those cares that have been our concern the work goes on, the cause endures, the hope still lives and the dream shall never die.

IT'S TIME TO GET AWESOME
post_text:
The Next Level
We're excited to take WI - ME Snowboards in a new direction. After rebuilding in 2018-2019, and with the start of a new decade, new people we decided it was time. WI-ME was my life story growing up in Janesville WI, and learning how to ski at 2 1/2 then finding snowboarding at age 12, and from there moving to Sugarloaf Maine to find an encouraging group that pushed me to pursue it professionally.

Well that story has changed, and evolved along the way. It's time to close this final chapter in this book, and begin the sequel.
I can't thank you enough for all your support, our message will still be the same. To all those cares that have been our concern the work goes on, the cause endures, the hope still lives and the dream shall never die.

IT'S TIME TO GET AWESOME

text:
Surrendering to the flow enough me back to this industry. I found at at 18 and did alright before I pursued snowboarding competitively. After I called it a career I was pretty banged up, luckily I found this amazing company through a friend. Running two businesses and consulting I literally didn’t have time.
My dad was back on snow 2 1/2 months later after having a triple bypass. After my family had amazing results with these products, I said alright I’m all in.
The story doesn’t end here, I had partners in my conventional business that didn’t support my decision. I fact they did everything they could to bury me. I walked away from 20k a month with our consulting firm, and was left holding the tab of 6 figures of debt.

Last year I dug my way out inch by inch. It was a massive uphill battle and lots of sacrifice. It’s not the destination it’s the path we take!

Last fall someone challenged me and said you’re ——ing brilliant what’s stopping you? I told the story above, and then got halfway into an excuse, and......I said wait, let me get back to you on that.

Then one day in @garythehammer’s basement it hit me, like a massive bolt of lightning. We have an amazing industry, and company, all these strategies I’ve used for fortune 5 to SMB’s could work for us. I called @chrismailhoit talking a million miles per hour about it!
From there I searched high and low for programs, loved them but their high ticket entries weren’t duplicatable for my good vibe tribe.
The idea of Influencer Academy was born. It’s time to level this playing field. All the top earners use these but don’t talk about it or know how to teach it. I’ve been teaching and coaching since I was 16, and this is why I’ve survived multiple near death accidents, gone through all the adversity, holy ^%#^ this is why I’m here!

Who’s ready?
Who’s ready to crush their goals?

Who wants this as bad as I do?

Who wants to empower all those that matter the most to free themselves from that 9-5?

Who wants to wake up everyday with a purpose?

I dare you to dream bigger! Patience, practice, persistence, builds that belief, that belief is what it takes to conquer fear, if you believe it you can achieve it

Hate to break it to you but...

😷 Allergy pills do not eliminate the source of your allergies.

👎 Taking weight loss products doesn’t fix the fact that your metabolism has slowed down!

🤦‍♀️ Applying zit cream does not stop you from having acne.

🍪 Avoiding gluten does not heal your gluten intolerance.

💢 Applying lotion to eczema does not address why you are getting it in the first place.

😴Taking a sleeping pill does not get rid of your insomnia.

😬 Taking Ibuprofen for chronic pain and inflammation does not address why you are hurting in the first place.

☕️ Drinking coffee does not fix your problem with fatigue.

➡️ What does?! 🤔 Getting to the root cause!

In most cases that is body imbalance, inflammation, and/or gut health.

Get to the cause instead of masking the symptoms! 💖

What if you had knowledge about getting to the root of that issue ? Would you be interested?

text:
Life’s too short to be pissed off.
.
.
.
I get it. I got stuck in the cycle of complaining and judging everyone & everything around me. It’s happens without warning. .
.
.
I got so fed up with with all the negativity that I decided I had enough. It was time to change. .
.
.
It’s not easy and it took time. I started with just tying to find one positive thing in my day. After a while, I’d try to find more. It was just a game I was playing in my own head.
.
.
.
After 6 months, I was enjoying my life so much more. My relationships with people became stronger. I was attracting better people around me. There was so much new opportunity. It’s crazy how it changed my life. .
.
.
.
If you struggle with being negative and judging people, please use me as an example. I was the same way. You can just look back at my old posts from a few years ago. I was feeding the negativity. This completely change my life. It just takes a decision to change!

@SHREDNECK1
Jeff “The Shredneck” Lavin

text:
Pay It Forward
.
.
I say this a lot.... I was incredibly fortunate to have such good guidance when I was young. I was able to learn through others experience and skipped a lot of pain and trials by doing so. .
.
.
I really want to start Giving Back a lot of the things I was taught and learned along the way. .
.
.
This was a big one and I think it applies to so many aspects of life. In business, relationships, investing, etc.
.
.
“Successful people make decisions very quickly once the facts are presented and they very rarely waiver on that decision. Unsuccessful people take a long time to make a decision and frequently change their mind”

This is how I used it in my life. I don’t make decisions blindly. If it’s an investment or an idea that I want to bring to life, I get as much info as possible so I can evaluate the risk along with upside. Don’t gamble. Take calculated risks. Once I have the info, I make my decision and jump all the way in.

I don’t ever get stuck in “analysis paralysis.” I go all in and I don’t waiver. I’m in it for the long run. Don’t give up when things gets hard. Don’t grab at every new trend or buzz word. Stay on track and ride it til the end.

text:
First, how's that even possible?

I mean, dude.

You're a coach, consultant, or network marketer.

Sellin' somethin' sweet.

Right?

Say a sale's worth $2k, lifetime.

K...

That's only 15 sales a month.

What if it's worth $3k?

Factoring-in residual and all?

Then you only need 10 sales.

$5k?

C'mon.

Anyone can do six sales in 30 days.

Now look.

I'm not tryin' to make you feel bad.

Really, I'm not.

But somebody's gotta be straight with ya.

This underachieving?

It's unacceptable.

And I'd rather be mauled by that bear from The Revenant than see you struggle.

So right here, right now, I'm gonna tell you what your problem is.

Ready for it?

Two words:

Information constipation.

Bam.

There's your diagnosis.

Too much searching, studying, reading, learning, considering, analyzing, optimizing, idolizing.

Not enough doing.

Seriously.

Sooner or later?

You gotta stop hidin' behind books, courses, coaching, conferences, and free Facebook groups.

And do the damn work.

Cuz no matter how smart you are?

Or how many gurus you pay to have fake friendships with?

Or how committed you are to self-improvement?

Or how many seminar selfies you take?

You can't make money without:

* An offer.
* Ads running.
* Videos playing.
* Emails sending.
* Calendars filling.
* Calls happenin'.

Amiright?

You know I am.

So if all you do is consume and never produce?

You'll never get to $30k/mo, amigo.

Now.

Don't get me wrong.

I'm all for investing in yourself.

And sharpening skills.

And networking.

And stayin' on the cutting-edge.

But if that's all you ever do?

No wonder your profit's plugged up.

So, again:

Less information.

More implementation.

That's the cure.

But the thing is?

Implementation's a mofo.

Isn't it?

You've got questions.

"Should I charge $3k or $4k?"

"What about pay plans?"

"How do I get 'em to go all-in?"

"Should I have new clients sign a contract?"

"How do I handle refund requests?"

"What should my opt-in video be about?"

"Who should I target for this facebook ad?"

"Do I exclude anyone?"

"The hell do I say in these emails?"

"How often do I send 'em?"

Plus:

You've got doubts.

"Why would anyone listen to me?"

"I just joined the company."

"I don't have any case studies."

"My website's ugly."

"I'm awful on video."

"Nobody's gonna pay this much."

"What if I get a bad review?"

"Maybe my family has a point."

"If I fail, everyone's gonna laugh at me."

Then:

You've got tech challenges.

"How do I create a custom conversion?"

"It says to paste this code in the <head> section of every page on my website."

"WTF does that even mean?"

"How do I connect ActiveCampaign to ClickFunnels?"

"Wait, should I even use ClickFunnels?"

"Or no?"

"What if I want a custom domain for my squeeze page - so it's nice and neat?"

"How do I go about that?"

"Why's the background image so blurry?"

"My logo looks like a hot mess on mobile."

"Can I have different availability for different sales guys?"

"But sync all the calls onto one Google Calendar?"

"How do I get that Proof plugin to show on this page, but not that one?"

"Wish I knew how to run an ad to people who booked a call but didn't buy."

"Can I auto-enroll new teammates into the training portal?"

"I can?"

"Sweet - how?"

Finally:

There's sh*t you hate doing.

"I want ads and emails like _______ has."

"But when it comes to copy, I don't know whether to check my ass or scratch my watch."

"Completely clueless."

"Plus, no way I could sit behind a computer all day, typin' away."

"Boooring!"

"Anyone know a word wizard for hire?"

"If so, what do they charge?"

"And how do I know if the cost is reasonable?"

Or:

"No way I'm doin' phone sales."

"Personally, I'd rather drink Chick-fil-A toilet water."

"So..."

"Whaddya recommend?"

"Just put a Buy Now button?"

"And hope they sign up on their own?"

"Or, like, where do I find a closer?"

"And how do I train him?"

"And how much do I pay him?"

"Ugh, I need a drink."

PAUSE.

I get it.

I see why nothing's gettin' done.

Why you'd rather bury yourself in a good book.

Or buy your fourth Facebook ads course.

Or hire your next high ticket mentor.

Than face all that overwhelm and uncertainty and suffering.

But what if you didn't have to?

What if you could just snap your fingers?

And eliminate everything sucky or scary about scalin' your biz?

Newsflash:

You can.

How?

Hire us.

And you should.

Cuz my guess is?

You'll always be unwilling or unable to do certain things that are required to hit $30k/mo.

Let alone $300k/mo.

So be honest with yourself.

Are you ever gonna see this thing through?

We risk sacrificing the opportunity to live a more fulfilling and purpose driven life. We risk sacrificing the opportunity to make a difference in the lives of others. We risk sacrificing the beautiful blessing of finding a greater sense of meaning in our own lives.
In short, we run the very real risk living a life of regret.

text:
Ask anyone how they got to the top of the mountain.

They’ll tell you left foot, right foot.
Inch by inch.

Not giving up.

Finding a different route when they got stuck.

Everything worthwhile is uphill.

Everything worthwhile is uphill.

I’ve been saying that a lot lately. Because it’s a fact. Almost everything that has value, almost everything that has purpose, requires work on our part to attain it. We have to put in the effort to get what to where we want to go.

Think about it – you want a good marriage? You have to work at it. You want a good career? You have to work at it. You want to change your life, achieve a goal, do something you’ve never done before? You have to work at it.

Nothing that is good in life comes easy. And very little that comes easy is good.

You have to work at it.

If everything worthwhile is uphill, that means you have to make the choice to go and get it. You have to put one foot in front of the other and take that hill a step at a time. You must grow and stretch yourself a little every day. You may not conquer a mountain at first, but for every hill you do conquer, you gain confidence for the next climb. And there is always another hill to start climbing from the bottom

text:
Date a girl who doesn't read. Find her in the weary squalor of a Midwestern bar. Find her in the smoke, drunken sweat, and varicolored light of an upscale nightclub. Wherever you find her, find her smiling. Make sure that it lingers when the people that are talking to her look away. Engage her with unsentimental trivialities. Use pick-up lines and laugh inwardly. Take her outside when the night overstays its welcome. Ignore the palpable weight of fatigue. Kiss her in the rain under the weak glow of a streetlamp because you’ve seen it in a film. Remark at its lack of significance. Take her to your apartment. Dispatch with making love. Fuck her.

Let the anxious contract you've unwittingly written evolve slowly and uncomfortably into a relationship. Find shared interests and common ground like sushi and folk music. Build an impenetrable bastion upon that ground. Make it sacred. Retreat into it every time the air gets stale or the evenings too long. Talk about nothing of significance. Do little thinking. Let the months pass unnoticed. Ask her to move in. Let her decorate. Get into fights about inconsequential things like how the fucking shower curtain needs to be closed so that it doesn't fucking collect mold. Let a year pass unnoticed. Begin to notice.

Figure that you should probably get married because you will have wasted a lot of time otherwise. Take her to dinner on the forty-fifth floor at a restaurant far beyond your means. Make sure there is a beautiful view of the city. Sheepishly ask a waiter to bring her a glass of champagne with a modest ring in it. When she notices, propose to her with all of the enthusiasm and sincerity you can muster. Do not be overly concerned if you feel your heart leap through a pane of sheet glass. For that matter, do not be overly concerned if you cannot feel it at all. If there is applause, let it stagnate. If she cries, smile as if you’ve never been happier. If she doesn't, smile all the same.

Let the years pass unnoticed. Get a career, not a job. Buy a house. Have two striking children. Try to raise them well. Fail frequently. Lapse into a bored indifference. Lapse into an indifferent sadness. Have a mid-life crisis. Grow old. Wonder at your lack of achievement. Feel sometimes contented, but mostly vacant and ethereal. Feel, during walks, as if you might never return or as if you might blow away on the wind. Contract a terminal illness. Die, but only after you observe that the girl who didn't read never made your heart oscillate with any significant passion, that no one will write the story of your lives, and that she will die, too, with only a mild and tempered regret that nothing ever came of her capacity to love.

Do those things, god damnit, because nothing sucks worse than a girl who reads. Do it, I say, because a life in purgatory is better than a life in hell. Do it, because a girl who reads possesses a vocabulary that can describe that amorphous discontent of a life unfulfilled—a vocabulary that parses the innate beauty of the world and makes it an accessible necessity instead of an alien wonder. A girl who reads lays claim to a vocabulary that distinguishes between the specious and soulless rhetoric of someone who cannot love her, and the inarticulate desperation of someone who loves her too much. A vocabulary, goddamnit, that makes my vacuous sophistry a cheap trick.

Do it, because a girl who reads understands syntax. Literature has taught her that moments of tenderness come in sporadic but knowable intervals. A girl who reads knows that life is not planar; she knows, and rightly demands, that the ebb comes along with the flow of disappointment. A girl who has read up on her syntax senses the irregular pauses—the hesitation of breath—endemic to a lie. A girl who reads perceives the difference between a parenthetical moment of anger and the entrenched habits of someone whose bitter cynicism will run on, run on well past any point of reason, or purpose, run on far after she has packed a suitcase and said a reluctant goodbye and she has decided that I am an ellipsis and not a period and run on and run on. Syntax that knows the rhythm and cadence of a life well lived.

Date a girl who doesn't read because the girl who reads knows the importance of plot. She can trace out the demarcations of a prologue and the sharp ridges of a climax. She feels them in her skin. The girl who reads will be patient with an intermission and expedite a denouement. But of all things, the girl who reads knows most the ineluctable significance of an end. She is comfortable with them. She has bid farewell to a thousand heroes with only a twinge of sadness.

Don’t date a girl who reads because girls who read are storytellers. You with the Joyce, you with the Nabokov, you with the Woolf. You there in the library, on the platform of the metro, you in the corner of the café, you in the window of your room. You, who make my life so goddamned difficult. The girl who reads has spun out the account of her life and it is bursting with meaning. She insists that her narratives are rich, her supporting cast colorful, and her typeface bold. You, the girl who reads, make me want to be everything that I am not. But I am weak and I will fail you, because you have dreamed, properly, of someone who is better than I am. You will not accept the life of which I spoke at the beginning of this piece. You will accept nothing less than passion, and perfection, and a life worthy of being told. So out with you, girl who reads. Take the next southbound train and take your Hemingway with you.

Or, perhaps, stay and save my life.

text:
Have you ever fired a mentor? I recently did, their views didn’t align with me when I saw this which he wrote the publisher and editor of a magazine.

“Hello my friend. You have always had my utmost respect. But…here is a word of advice. Take down all ads or anything you have on the net about your latest issue featuring lesbians. This is terribly offensive to most people and you may alienate, and probably have already, all of your readers. Unless I get reassurances from you that you will not do that again I cannot, and will not, endorse or promote your magazine any more. I cannot and will not endorse, directly or indirectly, homosexuality.”

I only had a few words for them, this is unacceptable, you’re irrelevant, you’re fired!

We all have our views, but when you push yours and bully others with your “influence” this is where the line gets drawn in the sand for me.

This is why it’s our generation’s time to step up and take the torch and lead the our posterity and their’s into the light. To all those cares that have been my concern, the work goes on, the cause endures, the hope still lives and the dream shall never die!

text:
Soooo, I went to an interview for a job👔 yesterday. I know your shocked 🤷🏼‍♂️

When the boss asked what I wanted for compensation💰 I replied......

1) "First I would like commission💲💲💲 on everything I sell, & I want to see that percentage get far higher ⬆as I improve.

2) I would also like the opportunity to receive free 🏖🚢trips, bonuses paid in full, and free marketing materials based on my performance.

3) I expect you to provide me with my own website 💻and provide free online training accessible all over the 🌎.

4) When I bring in any new sales people👫, I deserve a bonus 💲💲💲and to be compensated💰 a percentage of their sales and the sales of any new people🙋🏼 they bring in.

5) I would like the opportunity to rapidly advance within the company📈.

6) When I do well..... lots of praise🎉, recognition🎈, and more bonuses💰💲💰. Did I mention all expense paid trips for me and my spouse?☀️🚢🌴⛱✈️

7) I would like my friends👭 and family👪 to work here.

😎 By the way, I need to set my own schedule,📅 and only work when it suits me and my family💺.

So when can I start?!?!"

After the owner recovered from shock⚡, he roared with laughter. 😂😂😂😂 "

You must be crazy🙆🏼 or dreaming. You will NEVER🚫 find an opportunity like that 🌎ANYWHERE🌎 and if you do, come back and get me, cause I want to work there too!!"

......So I gave him my business card!!!!😉

You can have things on your terms. You have just been looking for it from the wrong people.

If it comes with a salary or hourly pay rate, they own you.

😎 By the way, I need to set my own schedule,📅 and only work when it suits me and my family💺.

So when can I start?!?!"

After the owner recovered from shock⚡, he roared with laughter. 😂😂😂😂 "

You must be crazy🙆🏼 or dreaming. You will NEVER🚫 find an opportunity like that 🌎ANYWHERE🌎 and if you do, come back and get me, cause I want to work there too!!"

......So I gave him my business card!!!!😉

You can have things on your terms. You have just been looking for it from the wrong people.

If it comes with a salary or hourly pay rate, they own you.

text:
“It’s all my fault.”

Even when it’s not.

I try my best to believe that.

No, it’s not easy.

It’s always tempting to make excuses.

Or place blame.

But if I don’t OWN IT, then what?

Then I’m not in control.

Am I?

Like if someone or something else is the reason I’m not happy/healthy/successful…

Well…

What does that make ME?

Helpless.

That’s what.

And that’s not a good feeling, is it?

Plus, if it’s outta my hands?

Why try?

See what I’m sayin’?

But when everything’s “my fault?”

I can change.

Can’t I?

I can become the man I want to be.

And so can you… when you decide to OWN YOUR SH*T!

Steve

text:
🔥Making an Impact vs Making an Income🔥

If I your neighbor lost their house in a fire tomorrow😱, or your best friend got diagnosed with cancer 😭(heaven forbid) and needed financial assistance to get back on their feet...would you hesitate to do everything you could to help them out?

I find it pretty hard to believe that anyone on my friends list would fall short of anything less than "hell yes I would!"🙋‍♂️🙋‍♀️

So, now let me ask you this, why is it that when there are people all around you that are struggling financially, going paycheck to paycheck, or are single parents working 3 jobs do you not go out of your way to help them out?🤔

🛑Let me clarify this...what I mean is...if you are in the network marketing arena would you agree that you have a means for anyone to make an extra couple hundred dollars a month???

Do you think that would be a BIG deal to someone who has little to no money for groceries, clothes for their kids, to make their car payment, or even their mortgage?👨‍👩‍👧
Lets do a little exercise. Put yourself in the position of someone who is drowning 😫, looking for a lifeline. Do you always broadcast to the world that things are rough financially?

Would you appreciate ANY idea someone tossed your way that could potentially help you get into a better position?😍
You never REALLY know what is going on in peoples lives, and who would or would not be open to this incredible gift 💌.

How about another angle 📐...how many doctors, lawyers, engineers, nurses, veterinarians, physical therapists, and executives have joined network marketing?🤔
a TON !!! why? Because for them it is all about time freedom ✨!

⌚Time for a reality check!! Now I mean all of this, with nothing but Love ♥️ and appreciation 🙏.

But, Do you really think it is your place to decide who would benefit from working in our industry, and in particular your company? Or do you think that is up to each person to decide for themselves?😮

so if your answer was the latter...you get a prize 🎉!! lol.

It is a hypothetical prize. But still give yourself a pat on the back👏.

The truth is, there are people who come into this industry skeptical only wanting to make a couple hundred dollars a month, and a few years later "caught the bug" and made millions🤑.

The truth is, there are people who reluctantly come into this industry thinking they will make nothing, nada, zilch and are now able to pay for their kids ⚽⚾🏀⛸️ month activities.

The truth is there are people who have been in this industry for 20 years and are simply happy to belong to a group of amazing people 😊 who all have common goals, a love and support of each other, and bring nothing but positivity to their life.

Does it matter??

Stop stressing over your income, and get out there an make an impact . There are people who this could REALLY change their lives.

And, if you wake-up each day🌞 with the purpose of making an impact in your heart, mind, and soul...the money will just be the icing on the cake 🍰!

Lets change the world!🌎

I find it pretty hard to believe that anyone on my friends list would fall short of anything less than "hell yes I would!"🙋‍♂️🙋‍♀️

Wasatch Project
July 26, 2019 at 7:22 AM ·

To All✨

One of my best friends and previous snowboard coaches left us in August 2018. My name is Mitchell Heberer

Dustin Linker started a program for skiers and snowboarders to train, travel, compete, film, learn and grow to become the best versions of themselves.

I am one of the athletes and students of this program. Dustin called us The Wasatch Project.

I later learned that Dustin had a vision to evolve the project into a charter school.

Since my friends passing I personally have had many life lessons and grief to grow and learn through.

I admire my friends vision and I want to carry that on and see how far this can go💨

I took over The Wasatch Project Facebook accounts and I am slowly bring this to life🌱

As Dustin would say, “Shred For The Cure!”

❤️

***I am asking you to join our group called The Wasatch Project. LINK BELOW.

https://www.facebook.com/groups/862652250572787/

This is a group I had previously started.

I want to keep this space available for us to connect, come together and keep The Wasatch Project Alive!

We are a positive space and all are welcome.

We have a tremendous vision for our future and through perseverance, community and communication we will become something good and leave a legacy🙏🏻

We are The Wasatch Project🏂

text:
Write down 10 goals you want to accomplish in the next 12 months
* Write in present tense

Take the list and really assess: if you could have any 1 of the goals achieved in the NEXT 24 hours, which would it be (BE HONEST) and circle it.

Take that one goal and run through the following:

* Write it down as clearly as you can (a 6-year old should be able to understand it)
* Set a deadline for achievement
* Brainstorm actions needed
* Make a checklist of highest impact actions to do regularly
* Commit to taking action
* Do something every day towards the most important goal

Seems easy enough right?

text:
“Entrepreneur’s Credo "

I do not choose to be a common man,
It is my right to be uncommon … if I can,
I seek opportunity … not security.

I do not wish to be a kept citizen.
Humbled and dulled by having the
State look after me.

I want to take the calculated risk;
To dream and to build.
To fail and to succeed.

I refuse to barter incentive for a dole;
I prefer the challenges of life
To the guaranteed existence;
The thrill of fulfillment
To the stale calm of Utopia.

I will not trade freedom for beneficence
Nor my dignity for a handout
I will never cower before any master
Nor bend to any threat.

It is my heritage to stand erect.
Proud and unafraid;
To think and act for myself,
To enjoy the benefit of my creations
And to face the world boldly and say:
This, with God’s help, I have done.

All this is what it means
To be an Entrepreneur.

text:
A year ago I was knocked down to the street by a freight train, today I'm back on my feet.

What it is, is how we react towards adversity.

What do you do in your darkest hour?

When you get that call at 3am?

Or realize you were being used by someone you knew for a long time?

Life will knock us down, it's how we get back up, it's how we rise to the occasion, and the challenge!

While this was a major hit it propelled me into what I’m supposed be doing, who I’m meant to be around, and align myself with!

When life hands you lemons, call your close friends and make vodka sours! Burn down the house, roast marshmallows, s’mores, sing campfire songs, reminisce about life.

Then the next day, level the foundation and start over. Build it stronger, with bricks, concrete steel, with a solid four corners!

A year goes by remember that you survived your darkest hour. You’re a heck of a lot stronger and have grown above and beyond. Enjoy who you became, take that moment, share it with the world on social media. Because somewhere someone is going through something similar and they need to hear this to go above and beyond!

text: We can choose not to take action, or we can choose to become significant. It’s that simple!
post_text: We can choose not to take action, or we can choose to become significant. It’s that simple!

text:
We can choose not to take action, or we can choose to become significant. It’s that simple.

I want to tell you about what made the biggest change in my life. I realized that I needed to change the people I surrounded myself with.

A year ago, I was visiting Denver, Colorado. I had a business partner who was quite well off with several flourishing businesses. One day we were getting food and somebody else had left $40 at the self-checkout. He took it. A minute later the lady who had left it behind came back. She was frantic about the $40 she’d lost but instead of handing it back, he pretended he didn’t have it. I turned to him and said, “You’d better give that back or we’re going to have some problems.”

Whether that was a learning experience for him or not, I don’t know. But it certainly was for me. It made me realize that I want to surround myself with people that share my values, my virtues, and my integrity.

Entrepreneurs often say you are the sum of the five people that you surround yourself with. A few years ago, I had surrounded myself with people that dragged me down. They didn’t want to support my greatness, my aspirations and the person I wanted to become. I was depressed, I was down, I was overweight, I didn't want to get off the couch.

Both in this example and the example of my business partner, the people around me didn’t change. They didn’t suddenly become different people. Instead, I realized I needed a different environment and I went looking for it. As a result, my life completely did a complete 180. My action threw me in a whole new direction and the universe responded with abundance.

I now have the right mentors, people who have multimillion-dollar businesses and want to show me how it’s done. I have the right coaches to help me take myself and my business to the next level. I have good friends that cheer me on, but also tell it like it is.

I believe that we're all made up of the same energy or matter. Whether you believe in a higher power or the power of the universe, there is something that links us all together. Everything happens for a reason and everything is a lesson. Another lesson I’ve learned from changing my environment is that you have to give up the good enough to find the great. When I split with my business partner there was loss involved. I had to give up part of my business. But I now have a business and a life that’s more aligned with who I am.

text:
Let’s pretend you’re Aladdin.

You rub your magic lamp

(Not as dirty as it sounds).

Out pops the big blue genie.

(Still not dirty. I swear.)

Blah blah blah, you get three wishes.

But Genie’s a little pressed for time so he narrows the list for you.

It’s the Mommy version.

Custom crafted for busy women like you.

Ready?

Here are your choices:

Earn more money
Work from anywhere
Have more time for yourself
Pay off debt
Put savings away for your future
Boost up your family’s vacation account
Turn your pet monkey into an elephant and marry a princess
Wait…

Genie just said he’s out of that last one.

But he feels bad about it, so...

Rather than give you 3 wishes?

He’s gonna give you everything else on the list.

But there’s one small catch…

Which seems fair after all…

I mean, he is granting you extra wishes.

Right?

See, rather than hand you everything you could easily waste in a week…

He’s making YOU the genie.

And teaching you how to make your wishes come true whenever you want.

Step-by-step instructions for ramping up your own revenue.

And building your own financial future.

Turning you into a great big lady boss.

No experience necessary.

And even though I’m talking about make-believe genies and rubbing lamps?

This story is entirely legit.

But I’m the Genie.

(Oooh, plot twist!)

And there’s no lamp.

And you’re already halfway to the good part.

You know how to do everything you need to.

You’re even doing it now.

You’re just not getting paid for it.

And sure, this sounds too good to be true, but...

It’s not.

And I’ll prove it to you - for free.

How?

Well, I filmed a lil’ video for you that explains it all.

I’ll show you how to make those money wishes come true.

In just a few hours a week.

(Way less than forty.)

And without any of the sketchy stuff you hate.

Like tech.

Or begging, cold-calling, and high-pressure sales tactics.

Because you’re Aladdin, remember?

The hero.

Not Jaffar.

The villain.

And I’m Jeff, by the way.

Your guide to the land of good things.

Like this free vid:

https://jeffssidehustle.com/video

Look…

I get it.

You’re wondering why I’m talking to you about a man with a monkey, and money.

Well, my hope is, you’ll like what I send you and want to ramp up your revenue quickly.

Because I’ve got a do-it-with-ya training program to get you going quicker.

Speed up your success story.

Turn you from lady pauper to Sheik Yaboody.

(Say that last part out loud.)

And if you want to work with me?

Howzabout you give this link a little clicky-click:

https://jeffssidehustle.com/video

And request a quick call with me.

Cool? Cool.

Talk soon.

- Jeff

JEFFSSIDEHUSTLE.COM
Start Your Side Hustle

text:
People are always asking me about the secrets and tricks I use to get results. Sorry if this disappoints you: There are no secrets. There are no tricks. If anything, it’s the opposite: Whether you’re a pro athlete or a guy running a business or driving a truck or going to school, it’s simple. Ask yourself where you are now, and where you want to be instead. Ask yourself what you’re willing to do to get there. Then make a plan to get there. Act on it.

1. Ask yourself: Where are you now?
2. Ask yourself: Where do you want to be instead?
3. Ask yourself: What are you willing to do to get there?
4. Make a plan to get there.
5. Act on it.

text:
Too much and too long, we seem to have surrendered community excellence and community values in the mere accumulation of material things. Our gross national product…if we should judge the United States of America by that – counts air pollution and energy drink advertising, and ambulances to clear our highways of carnage. It counts special locks for our doors and the jails for those who break them. It counts the destruction of our redwoods and the loss of our natural wonder in chaotic sprawl. It counts napalm and the cost of a nuclear warhead, and armored cars for police who fight riots in our streets. It counts Whitman’s rifle and Speck’s knife, and the glorification of violence in order to sell toys to our children.

Yet the gross national product does not allow for the health of our children, the quality of their education, or the joy of their play. It does not include the beauty of our poetry or the strength of our marriages; the intelligence of our public debate or the integrity of our public officials. It measures neither our wit nor our courage; neither our wisdom nor our learning; neither our compassion nor our devotion to our country; it measures everything, in short, except that which makes life worthwhile. And it tells us everything about America except why we are proud that we are Americans.

Some men see things the way they are and ask why, I dream things that never were and say why not. The time is now for us to carry the torch for ourselves, for our country, for our posterity and their’s to lead us to a better light.

I. JUST. FOUND. OUT....the (REAL) Erin Brockovich has joined MY company’s board of directors‼️

“I am proud to join the family in this capacity at this important time in the company’s history,” Brockovich said. “This is a company I have admired at arm’s length for some time. 💁‍♀️

It’s a company with strong momentum – not just in the U.S. – but globally. In today’s world, actively managing our health has never been so vital. 💪🏻

🙋‍♀️By the same token, it’s never been so easy and accessible. This company is helping people from every walk of life better manage and optimize their health, and I’m excited to be the newest member of the the biohacker community.”

-Erin Brockovich

Brockovich has over 35 years of diverse public health, legal, and business successes, both domestically and globally, and is one of the most requested speakers on the international lecture circuit. 🎤

As President of Brockovich Research & Consulting, she is currently doing consulting work for three national law firms, involved in numerous environmental projects worldwide, and writing her fourth book scheduled for release next spring.📉📈

Raised in a family of athletes and nutrition advocates, she has a deep-rooted passion for health and nutrition and has spent the better part of the past two decades sharing that passion on a global stage. 👩‍👧‍👦

#NextLevel #Anti-Inhibitions

text:
It has never been easier to start a company than right now.

ANZ offers an entire company setup in one day, even with a website and logo.

The entire small business and start-up ecosystems therefore need to stop putting significant energy into attracting more people to launch startups and start businesses.

They can and will do it themselves.

We must instead now double down on commercialising these new businesses.

We must teach these founders how to sell their products and services.

We must coach them on growth.

The creation of more startups will create jobs.

However, we will see exponentially more jobs created if/when we commercialise and grow these startups.

The biggest risk we face is a bubble popping in a few years because this entire startup ecosystem we are building forgot to focus on commercialisation.

We need sales, much more than investment.

So we must teach how to pitch to customers, not investors.

text:
Everything worthwhile is uphill.

I’ve been saying that a lot lately. Because it’s a fact. Almost everything that has value, almost everything that has purpose, requires work on our part to attain it. We have to put in the effort to get what to where we want to go.

Think about it – you want a good marriage? You have to work at it. You want a good career? You have to work at it. You want to change your life, achieve a goal, do something you’ve never done before? You have to work at it.

Nothing that is good in life comes easy. And very little that comes easy is good.

You have to work at it.

If everything worthwhile is uphill, that means you have to make the choice to go and get it. You have to put one foot in front of the other and take that hill a step at a time. You must grow and stretch yourself a little every day. You may not conquer a mountain at first, but for every hill you do conquer, you gain confidence for the next climb. And there is always another hill to start climbing from the bottom

text:
“If you want something bad enough, you need to go out and make it happen.”
.
.

When I wanted to get sponsored, I hit up every company out there and sent them my video. If they didn’t respond, I sent another. I didn’t let the companies that said NO discourage me from my goal. .
.
.
With @wi_mesnowboards , I didn’t just tell everyone I wanted to start a snowboard brand. I didn’t get trapped in feeling like I had to know more than anyone on the planet about branding. I didn’t let the people who said,” it’s really competitive” get to me. I just went for it and made it happen. .
.
.
I really just wanted to say this for all the people who want to follow their dreams. Who want to move on an opportunity. Who want to start a company, but something is holding them back. Lack of confidence, their parents, whatever...
.
.
.
You Got This!!! .
.
.
if I can do it, so can you. I’m not smarter than anyone who’s following me. I’m not any more special. It was the simple fact that I just went for it.
.
.
Whatever is holding you back, please make today the day you choose to go for it!!!

text:
Life’s too short to be pissed off.
.
.
.
I get it. I got stuck in the cycle of complaining and judging everyone & everything around me. It’s happens without warning. .
.
.
I got so fed up with with all the negativity that I decided I had enough. It was time to change. .
.
.
It’s not easy and it took time. I started with just tying to find one positive thing in my day. After a while, I’d try to find more. It was just a game I was playing in my own head.
.
.
.
After 6 months, I was enjoying my life so much more. My relationships with people became stronger. I was attracting better people around me. There was so much new opportunity. It’s crazy how it changed my life. .
.
.
.
If you struggle with being negative and judging people, please use me as an example. I was the same way. You can just look back at my old posts from a few years ago. I was feeding the negativity. This completely change my life. It just takes a decision to change!

text:
Taiwan is a pretty country! Not too many people in the west understand the history and difference between PRC and ROC.

The republic of China started in the early 1900s after Sun Yet Shen overthrew the Xing dynasty on his 11th try.

In the 1940s the USSR sent troops to bordering areas by the 1950s mainland became the People’s Republic Of China ( PRC ).

Anyone that had the means went to Taiwan 🇹🇼 where the ROC is now. People are very nice, and everyone speaks English. I look forward to returning soon!

text:
You can do anything if you put your mind to it! I started out in the trades as a welder and pipe fitter. When I was younger college wasn’t for me, I was more hands on.

In my 20s I followed a dream of pursing a career in snowboarding. It took me all over the country and world. I met so many amazing people. After I was done I started my own brand @wi_mesnowboards and went back to the trades to pay the bills.

What happened was an evolution, 8 years later as I look at my resume I’m proud of the skills I learned along the way of doing international business, and trade. I’m so stoked to be doing so many amazing things and connecting with amazing people.

If I could offer any advice for following your dream, it’d be three words “just do it!”

Most people negotiate the price of success so long that they would have been there by now had they paid it!

text: Life is tough that's a given, when you stand up you're going to be shoved back down, when you're down you're going to be stepped on, My advice doesn't come with any bells and whistles it's no secret you'll fall down, stumble, be pushed, you'll land square on your face. but everytime that happens you get back on your feet, remember that Success is defined as getting up one more time than you've been knocked down.

text:
Feb 24th 2006 I blew out my right ACL and finished out and had surgery in April. Then Dec 2006 I blew out my Left ACL and meniscus 4 days into my season. Sponsors dropped me, people asked when are you going to give up and get a real job. They me to find a a safer hobby.

I didn’t let them get to me or in the way of my dreams. Rather I subscribed to people that told me I can and will. I got back on that board, and a year later I was riding solid again. Don’t listen to the noise of others telling you how to live your life when they can’t figure how to live their’s. The only voice you should listen to is the one right in between your ears.

Have the courage to follow your heart and intuition, they already know what you truly want to become!

Jacob Gage
January 15, 2019 at 9:54 PM ·

Progression Monthly is designed for;

✅Entrepreneurs
✅Professionals
✅Sales Professionals
✅Speakers
✅Authors, and
✅Coaches
that desire to create extraordinary results in their life.

These individuals are searching for strategies to implement that will increase their income, increase their influence, and grow their impact.

Inside Andy Audate takes you on a deep-dive into;

Self Leadership Training: How do you design a leadership plan for yourself to produce your goals in a shorter time, saving you over 23% of your time.

Telling Your Story + Building Credibility: If you’ve ever doubted your ability to help people or identify as a thought leader, this subscription will help to reposition the way you perceive yourself and the vital work of which you’re capable in the thought leader space.

Why People Will Buy From YOU...Forever: You’ll discover the evolution of Andy's relationship with his students and fans, and how he reached the definitive long-term career stage of the process. Andy shares with you both philosophically and tactically how you can get people to buy from you forever.

What You Should (and Shouldn't) Sell: Do you want to figure out how to break down content, but don’t know how? What should you sell and what should you not sell? In this lesson, you will glean incredible insight and direction from Andy experience selling hundreds of thousands of dollars of products to over 23,450 people.

Create Blockbuster Curriculum + Courses: How exactly do you go about making module #1 of a course, or chapter 1 of a book, or even the first day of a webinar or live cast? What different facets do you need to think through in order to arrive at your most pertinent content as well as the best order for your students to understand this content? Andy breaks it down in this subscription.

Secrets to Help Your Clients Achieve More: Andy will share with you 10 ideas on how to become a higher level trainer.

And Much, Much more!

All for less than the cost of lunch!

Comment for more info.

text: When people want to win they will go to desperate extremes. However, anyone that has already won in life has come to the conclusion that there is no game. There is nothing but learning in this life and it is the only thing we take with us to the grave—knowledge. If you only understood that concept then your heart wouldn’t break so bad. Jealousy or revenge wouldn’t be your ambition. Stepping on others to raise yourself up wouldn’t be a goal. Competition would be left on the playing field, and your freedom from what other people think about you would light the pathway out of a dark place!

Even if we don't say it out loud or write it down, we all have a plan of where we want to be in the next 5 years.

We all definitely have the vision of how much we want to be earning in the future or which area, city, state or country we want to be living in etc etc

But what if you could get there in 12 months instead of 5 years?

What would you need to do differently to get to your goal in one-fifth of the time?

If you can't answer that yourself right now, that's ok!

I've taken some of the work out for you in this weeks video and podcast.

It's called The True Cost of Success and one of the points I cover is answering how you can get to where you want to in the shortest time.

You can watch the listen to the podcast right now by clicking here https://www.podomatic.com/…/episo…/2018-11-20T12_02_03-08_00

Or Watch by scrolling down the feed to yesterdays video.

Enjoy

Adam :-)

I was sold on a line of products for years that I thought were clean and good for my hair, or the crap I’d use on the road. They made my hair feel great versus anything else I had tried.
I then learned about an app called Think Dirty 👉Look it up!

My hair care line came up as an 8️⃣ 😲. What?!?! This was salon grade, super HIGH END, expensive product and turns out it’s TERRIBLE for me and my hair, YEEPS!!!! 👉THEN I learned about a hair product line pre-launching on the market and I had an opportunity to test it before it officially launched. WHAT!!!! SO COOL!!!! I’ve never been able to be apart of a “pre-launch” of a game changing product line. HECK YES!! Count me in!!! And.... it comes up as a 1️⃣ and 2️⃣ on Think Dirty... What?!?! It’s super clean for both me and the environment?!?!? Sounds awesome, but wait... 👉Let’s be frank - While it was cool to be apart of a pre-launch and for a product line that is super clean, THIS IS MY HAIR and Beard we are talking about. I have to love what I’m using!

And I love that there are clean hair care products out there, but they simply just don’t provide results.

HOLY MOLY!! SEE RESULTS BELOW (mine and others)👇👇👇👇 AND.... I CAN wash my hair ✨EVERY DAY✨ and NOT STRIP MY HAIR OF IT’S OILS?!?!?! (🎤 drop!) ✔️SOLD!!!!! Now, I gotta share this with you! Or message me here.
Hugs and high fives y’all!

Dustin Linker is the founder of the Wasatch Project.

The Wasatch Project is for dedicated intermediate to advanced freeskiers and snowboarders trying to reach their maximum potential.

The Wasatch Project teaches character development, mountain safety, and the most progressive freeskiing and snowboarding techniques, all while having fun!

Wether you're trying to make it to the next level by traveling and filming, or you have a strong passion for competition, this program has the steps and opportunities to get you there.

We have a range of programs available to meet the needs of each athlete.

Today we stand by the values that were intended as we evolve The Wasatch Project into a community of like minds to peruse a similar passion!

We hope you enjoy this page as we continue the Wasatch Project!

R.I.P. Dustin Linker 07/06/1977 – 08/30/2018

text:
Did you know that if you text "Home" to 741741 when you are feeling depressed, sad, or going through any kind of emotional crisis, a crisis worker will text you back immediately and continue to text with you? Many people, especially younger ones, prefer text to talking on the phone. It's a free service to anyone-- teens, adults, etc.-- who lives in the US.
Depression is real, you are not alone.
#youAREloved #youAREenough #youareNOTalone 💛

If you would like to join me in raising awareness for mental illness copy and paste (not share). Too many people are struggling and you can be the needed light. #Attitudeisgratitude

What’s the difference between impossible and possible? Two letters 😱💥

It means unsubscribing from the nay sayers✌️

And subscribing to the yay sayers that believe in you.

Then take those two letters ➡️IM⬅️

And trade them for ➡️EXTRA⬅️

Place the EXTRA in front of ordinary and you get❗️

EXTRAORDINARY💥

this mindset can change you hour, day, week, month, and year, or even your career! 😱🤟🤙

Our love for XBALM is at the core of how we came to own the business. Living in the mountains of Northern Utah, with it's extreme temperatures, we found ourselves always in need of XBALM. Whether we were hitting the slopes or enjoying the lake we had to have XBALM with us at all times. After falling in love with XBALM as a consumer, we found it increasingly hard to find it in the marketplace. in pursuit of the product we loved, we eventually found ourselves purchasing the company. We can't live with our XBALM and we understand it's users feel the same way! You live an amazing (and often extreme) life and XBALM is there to protect your lips while you live it!
